accessibility.text: (a) 'ben' is for 'son of'. It begins with a Beyth בּ which transliterates to the letter \"b\" in English.  Notice the בּ in the word בֶּן. the short ‘e’ sound is shown by a sehgol ֶ  which are the three little dots under the בּ.
(b) 'bath'  is 'daughter of'. It ends with a letter thaw ת 'th' . Notice the thaw in בַת. The short 'a' sound is shown by a Pathakh which is the small horizontal line ַ  beneath the בּ
(c) 'melekh' is the word for 'King'. notice the letters  miaeem  מ 'm' and lameth  ל 'l' and kaph ךְ 'kh' in the word  מֶלֶךְ
